## [ ] 7. PWA / Offline Mode

**Intent:** Package the app as a Progressive Web App so it can be installed on desktop
and mobile and continue working offline or on flaky connections. Depends on #5 so the
full data model is in place before designing the offline cache strategy.

**Details:**
- Add a Web App Manifest (`manifest.json`): app name, icons (192px, 512px), theme color,
  `display: standalone`, start URL.
- Implement a Service Worker with a cache-first strategy for all static assets
  (HTML, JS, CSS, engine HTML files, tutorial JSON).
- For authenticated users, cache the active project's pages in IndexedDB (via the
  service worker) so maps are readable and editable offline.
- Sync queue: changes made offline are written to a local queue and flushed to Firestore
  when connectivity returns (using the Background Sync API where supported).
- Offline indicator in the nav bar status area (already has `#host-status` dot).
- Install prompt: after 3 sessions, show a subtle "Install Multi Map" banner.

---

## [ ] 8. Node Search / Global Jump

**Intent:** Extend the existing nav search bar from single-map title search to cross-map
semantic search across all pages in the active project. Depends on #6 (AI enhancements)
so AI-driven node selection and search use the same underlying mechanism.

**Details:**
- Current search filters `state.nodes` by title substring — keep this as the instant
  local result tier.
- Add a second tier: cross-map search across all library pages (by title, content,
  node type), surfacing results with `[Page Name] › Node Title` breadcrumbs.
- Selecting a cross-map result: opens (or creates) a portal to that page and
  `selectNode()` on the matched node.
- Keyboard shortcut: `Cmd/Ctrl + K` opens the search bar with focus.
- Semantic / fuzzy search: use a lightweight client-side fuzzy matcher (e.g. Fuse.js)
  for typo tolerance; for AI-powered semantic search, pass the query to a
  `/api/search` Cloud Function that embeds and vector-searches across log-stored maps.

---

## [ ] 9. Undo / Redo Polish

**Intent:** The current undo system (`kernel.history`) clears on every portal
`enter` / `exit` and does not support redo. Improve to multi-level undo that persists
across portal navigation and adds a redo stack.

**Details:**
- Maintain separate undo/redo stacks per `map_id` (keyed in a `Map` object on the
  kernel) so entering and exiting a portal does not destroy the parent map's history.
- On `enterPortal`, push the current state onto the child map's history; the parent
  map's history is frozen but preserved.
- On `exitPortal`, restore the parent map's history stack.
- Redo stack: when `saveHistory()` is called (i.e. a new action is taken), clear the
  redo stack for that map — standard linear undo model.
- Cap history depth at 50 entries per map to limit memory.
- Keyboard: `Ctrl/Cmd+Z` = undo, `Ctrl/Cmd+Shift+Z` = redo.
- Show current undo depth as a subtle counter on the undo button (`↩️ 3`).

---

## [ ] 10. Map Sharing / Public Links

**Intent:** Allow users to share a read-only link to any map in their library.
Depends on #2 (auth) and #5 (project/pages) for the Firestore path structure.

**Details:**
- Add a `shared: boolean` flag (already exists on map meta) and a `share_token: string`
  field to the map schema.
- "Share" action in the Data Manager generates a unique `share_token` (UUID), sets
  `shared: true`, and writes the map to a public Firestore collection:
  `shared_maps/{share_token}` — read-only, no auth required.
- Public URL format: `https://mm.forestneff.com/view/{share_token}`.
- A lightweight `view.html` page renders the shared map in read-only map mode
  (no inspector, no AI, no editing controls).
- Shared maps show a "Fork to my workspace" button for authenticated visitors.
- Revoke sharing: sets `shared: false` and deletes the `shared_maps` document.
- Expiry option: shared links can optionally expire after 7 / 30 / 90 days.

---

## [ ] 11. Refine / Update Tutorial System — Reflect New Features & Ensure Auto-Nav

**Intent:** Bring the tutorial system up to date with all features added since initial
build (Person maps, portal save-on-exit, smart action button, type selector grouping,
phase engine visibility rules, etc.) and make tutorials drive the UI automatically
rather than requiring the user to navigate manually between steps. Done last — tutorials
should document the finished product, not a moving target.

**Details:**

### Content Updates
- **New tutorials needed:**
  - "Creating a Person Map" — person-root node, profile fields, child note auto-sync,
    Person phase engine view.
  - "Working with Portals" — creating a portal, linking to a library map, entering,
    editing the submap, exiting (with auto-save), the smart action button.
  - "Using the Smart Action Button" — context-sensitive actions per node type.
  - "Web Architect" — web-root map, node types (hero, section, card, footer),
    template application, Visual Editor phase view.
- **Update existing tutorials** to reflect renamed types (`person-root` vs old
  `user-profile`), new inspector type-selector grouping, and phase engine button
  visibility rules.

### Auto-Navigation
- Each tutorial step should be able to specify an `autoNav` field:
  ```json
  { "autoNav": { "view": "map" | "web" | "person" | "prompt" | "agent" } }
  ```
  When the tutorial advances to that step, `SC.setView(step.autoNav.view)` is called
  automatically.
- Steps can also specify `autoSelect: "<nodeId or nodeType>"` to auto-focus a node
  in the map.
- Steps should be able to highlight a specific DOM element with a pulsing ring overlay
  (tutorial spotlight) by specifying `spotlight: "<css-selector>"`.
- "Next" button in the tutorial panel should only activate once the user has completed
  the step's required action (e.g. added a node, changed a type), validated via a
  `validate` callback registered per step — or fall back to manual advance if no
  validator is defined.
- Tutorial progress persisted to localStorage so a refresh doesn't restart from step 1.
- "Restart Tutorial" button in the tutorial selection modal.

